<item>
            <title>[HBASE-5890] SplitLog Rescan BusyWaits upon Zk.CONNECTIONLOSS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5890</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We ran into a production issue yesterday where the SplitLogManager tried to create a Rescan node in ZK.  The createAsync() generated a KeeperException.CONNECTIONLOSS that was immedately sent to processResult(), createRescan node with --retry_count was called, and this created a CPU busywait that also clogged up the logs.  We should handle this better.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12553186">HBASE-5890</key>
            <summary>SplitLog Rescan BusyWaits upon Zk.CONNECTIONLOSS</summary>
